2026-04-17 | Minimum Distance of Mirror Pair

	Question
Return minimum distance or -1 if no pair exists.

	Approach
1.	Define function to reverse number.  

2.	Use hashmap:
		value → last seen index  

3.	Traverse array:
		for each index i:
			rev = reverse(nums[i])  

4.	If rev exists in map:
		update answer:
			ans = min(ans, i - lastIndex[rev])  

5.	Update map:
		store current index for nums[i]  

	Time Complexity
	O(n × digits)

	Space Complexity
	O(n)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:

    int reverseNum(int x){
        int rev = 0;
        while(x > 0){
            rev = rev * 10 + x % 10;
            x /= 10;
        }
        return rev;
    }

    int minMirrorDistance(vector<int>& nums) {

        unordered_map<int,int> mp;
        int ans = INT_MAX;

        for(int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++){

            int rev = reverseNum(nums[i]);

            if(mp.count(rev)){
                ans = min(ans, i - mp[rev]);
            }

            mp[nums[i]] = i;
        }

        return ans == INT_MAX ? -1 : ans;
    }
};

	Key Insight
Instead of checking all pairs:
we store previously seen values  

For each number:
		check if its reverse was seen before  

This reduces complexity from O(n²) → O(n).
